{"lemma": "شَطْرٌ", "slug": "شَطْرٌ", "root": "ش.ط.ر", "root_slug": "ش-ط-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ش-ط-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "شَطْر", "root": "شطر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 5}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["noun", "prep", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n22358"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "half", "fa": "نیم", "ur": "آدھا", "tr": "yarı", "id": "setengah", "bn": "অর্ধেক", "es": "mitad", "fr": "moitié", "de": "Hälfte", "ru": "половина", "zh": "一半"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to divide, to split, to halve"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "half, part"}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "towards", "examples": [{"text": "فَوَلِّ وَجْهَكَ شَطْرَ الْمَسْجِدِ الْحَرَامِ", "english": "So turn thy face toward the Inviolable Place of Worship"}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Probably a native doublet of سَطَرَ (saṭara)."}, "ipa": ["/ʃa.tˤa.ra/", "/ʃatˤr/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n22358", "headword_ar": "شَطْرٌ", "root": "$Tr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "half"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing; (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aTiyrN", "text_ar": "شَطِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$oTurN", "text_ar": "اَشْطُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K) and [of mult.]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$uTuwrN", "text_ar": "شُطُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) It is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AuHolubo HalabFA laka $aToruhu", "text_ar": "اُحْلُبْ حَلَبًا لَكَ شَطْرُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Milk thou a milking of which half shall be for thee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S.) And one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aEarN $aToraAni", "text_ar": "شَعَرٌ شَطْرَانِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Hair"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "half"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "black and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "half"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "white."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.) Accord. to Ibráheem El-Harbee, (O,) the saying of the Prophet,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano manaEa SadaqapF faA_in~aA A=xi*uwhaA", "text_ar": "مَنْ مَنَعَ صَدَقَةً فَاـِنَّا ا=خِذُوهَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wa$aTora maAlihi", "text_ar": "وَشَطْرَ مَالِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Whoso refuses to render a poor-rate, verily we take it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from him,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and half of his property"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], thus related by Bahz, is a mistake, and the right wording is,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wa$uTira maAluhu", "text_ar": "وَشُطِرَ مَالُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and his property shall be divided into two halves,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the collector of the poor-rate shall have the option given him and shall take that rate from out of the better of the two halves, as a punishment for the man's refusal of the rate; (O, K;) but it is said that this law was afterwards abrogated: (O:) Esh-Sháfi'ee, however, says that, in the old time, when one refused the poor-rate of his property, it was taken from him, and half of his property was taken as a punishment for his refusal; and he adduces this trad. as evidence thereof; but says that in recent times, only the poor-rate was taken from him, and this trad. was asserted to be abrogated. (TA. [More is there said on this subject, but I omit it as unprofitable.]) ―         -b2-  It occurs in two trads. as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Half a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mak~uwk", "text_ar": "مَكُّوك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.], or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "half a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wasoq", "text_ar": "وَسْق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.], of barley. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [In prosody,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Half a verse."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b4-  Also (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A part,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "portion,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "somewhat,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a thing; (Mgh, K;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aTiyrN", "text_ar": "شَطِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) In the trad. of the night-journey,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawaDaEa $aTorahaA", "text_ar": "فَوَضَعَ شَطْرَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means (assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And He remitted"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "part,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "somewhat, thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;) i. e., of the prayer. (TA.) And similar is the saying in another trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlT~ahuwru $aToru AlA_iymaAni", "text_ar": "الطَّهُورُ شَطْرُ الاـِيمَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Purification is part of faith"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Either the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fore pair"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hind pair of the teats"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a she-camel: she has two pairs of teats, a fore pair and a hind pair, and each pair is thus called: (S, K:) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "either of the two teats"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a ewe or she-goat: (IAar, TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$oTurN", "text_ar": "اَشْطُرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, TA.) Hence the saying, (S,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Halaba Ald~ahora A^a$oTurahu", "text_ar": "حَلَبَ الدَّهْرَ اَشْطُرَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one has known,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tried, varieties of fortune:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, * TA:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has experienced the good and evil of fortune;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its straitness and its ampleness:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being likened to one who has milked all the teats of a camel, that which yields plenty of milk and that which does not; the fore pair being the good; and the hind pair, the evil: or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$oTur", "text_ar": "اَشْطُر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "streams,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "flows, of milk:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and [in like manner] one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Halaba Ald~ahora $aTorayohi", "text_ar": "حَلَبَ الدَّهْرَ شَطْرَيْهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) And, as is said in the “ Kámil ” of Mbr, one says of a man experienced in affairs,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN qado Halaba", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ قَدْ حَلَبَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a$oTurahu", "text_ar": "اَشْطُرَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one has endured the difficulties and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "enjoyed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the ampleness of fortune, and managed his affairs in poverty and in wealth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "lit.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "has milked his pairs of teats,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "one pair after another. (TA.) ―         -b6-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A direction"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in which one looks or goes or the like. (S, A, Msb, K.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaSada $aTorahu", "text_ar": "قَصَدَ شَطْرَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He went in his,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its, direction; towards him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A.) And it is said in the Kur [ii. 139 and 144 and 145],"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawal~i wajohaka $aTora A@lomasojidi A@loHaraAmi", "text_ar": "فَوَلِّ وَجْهَكَ شَطْرَ ا@لْمَسْجِدِ ا@لْحَرَامِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Then turn thou thy face in the direction of the Sacred Mosque."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Fr, S.) The noun in this sense has no verb belonging to it: or one says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aTara $aTorahu", "text_ar": "شَطَرَ شَطْرَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[expl. above: see 1]. (K.) ―         -b7-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Distance,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remoteness."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "K", "O", "IAar"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}